Outgoing Correctional Services Principal Secretary (PS) Zeinab Hussein. [Courtesy]  Correctional Services Principal Secretary (PS) Zeinab Hussein has been transferred to Tourism ministry in the same capacity.  Her counterpart, Safina Kwekwe of the Tourism ministry, now moves the opposite direction, replacing Hussein at the correctional services docket.  The changes were made by President Uhuru Kenyatta on Tuesday, December 14.  Hussein has been directed to prepare hand-over notes for prompt transition. This comes on the back of scrutiny into correctional services docket after an increase in cases of prison break in recent times.  On November 16, news broke that three convicted terrorists had escaped from the highly-guarded Kamiti Maximum Prison.  The trio would be found in Kitui three days later.  By Paul Ogemba | 10 minutes ago By Patrick Muinde | 1 hour ago By Kamau Muthoni | 2 hours ago By Jacinta Mutura | 6 hours ago Enjoy unlimited access to The Standard website at a 50% discount on the yearly plan.